snippet: The United States has withdrawn a negotiating team from Pakistan in the latest sign that talks to reopen NATO supply routes into Afghanistan remain stalemated, American officials said.
abstract: United States withdraws a low-level negotiating team from Pakistan in the latest sign that talks to reopen NATO supply routes into Afghanistan remain in stalemate.

byline.original: By ERIC SCHMITT and DECLAN WALSH
byline.contributor: Eric Schmitt reported from Washington, and Declan Walsh from Islamabad, Pakistan.

lead_paragraph: The United States has withdrawn a negotiating team from Pakistan in the latest sign that talks to reopen NATO supply routes into Afghanistan remain stalemated, American officials said.

headline.seo: U.S. Negotiating Team Withdraws From Pakistan
headline.main: U.S. Takes Step Toward Exit in Pakistan Talks
